33:32.173 --> 33:42.525
You said before that your dad ran for sheriff and he 
was a little bit interested

33:32.173 --> 33:42.525
in politics. He was a Democrat like everybody was 
in Texas at the time. Yeah, he was a Democrat. Let's

33:47.451 --> 33:51.075
talk a little bit about his and then philosophy or 
political philosophy? Were you moderates,

33:54.130 --> 33:56.993
liberals, conservatives? What did you consider 
yourself? I think we have to temper

34:00.457 --> 34:13.172
almost anything with a recognition of the 
communication situation back in those days. I

34:14.213 --> 34:21.602
think one could say liberal or conservative

34:14.213 --> 34:21.602
and it really wouldn't

34:25.463 --> 34:32.552
measure

34:25.463 --> 34:32.552
one's philosophy then.

34:36.978 --> 34:39.482
My dad was just a straight Democrat. He had no room 
for the Republicans or anybody else for that

34:41.965 --> 34:52.860
matter. But the issues were so different. I don't 
know what he would be if he were alive today. Well,

35:01.655 --> 35:03.177
what did he feel about prohibition? He thought 
that it would be a good idea if he could make it, as a

35:05.320 --> 35:13.872
practical matter, make it go, but he didn't think 
he could. And so he was against it. I mean, he was for

35:17.898 --> 35:24.327
leaving things alone, not for the amendment. What 
did you think about Franklin Roosevelt and the New

35:24.796 --> 35:29.781
Deal? Well, at that time I was gone, and since that 
was the height of the Depression I was kind of busy,

35:29.801 --> 35:37.128
I'll tell you for sure. So, I really don't know. I

35:40.851 --> 35:45.075
just don't know. He was very bitter about Hoover, 
but I don't know whether that was just because

35:46.216 --> 35:52.542
Hoover was a Republican or because he really had a 
different kind of judgment on the economic

35:52.927 --> 35:56.831
situation. Did your father ever, do you know, even 
though you were gone, did your father ever

35:56.851 --> 36:02.917
accepted any government aid during the New Deal? 
No, absolutely not. He didn't go for that talk, not

36:06.360 --> 36:11.005
any, in any form. He considered accepting aid as a 
damned insult to his capabilities to make a living

36:11.025 --> 36:18.732
for himself and his family. He wouldn't have 
accepted one if he had been starving to death. Now,

36:25.492 --> 36:28.457
what about your political philosophy? Well, I 
grew up there as a Democrat. As a matter of fact,

36:32.523 --> 36:44.720
when you mentioned that, I was thinking about a 
time

36:32.523 --> 36:44.720
when I was a little kid when there was a Republican 
president elected, and I've forgotten which one

36:32.523 --> 36:44.720
right now. But he threw out the postmaster. who was 
a Democrat, and appointed a new postmaster, whom I

36:50.690 --> 36:57.197
heard my dad say was a goddamn Republican.

36:59.780 --> 37:06.787
And he was talking to a neighbor about this damn 
Republican up there as a postmaster.

37:06.807 --> 37:15.617
So we were going to go to town in a few days, and I went 
with him once to the post office, because I wanted

37:06.807 --> 37:15.617
to see this, this Republican.

37:19.478 --> 37:27.687
So we, I went to the post office with my father, and 
he knew the man of course, I didn't.

37:27.707 --> 37:37.898
And he spoke to him, called him Stratkins, and we 
talked for quite a little while there, and we got

37:27.707 --> 37:37.898
out of the post office, I said, so I think he was a 
pretty nice man. Dad said, well he's a fine man if he

37:40.200 --> 37:43.063
just wasn't a damn Republican. But I had never seen 
one, I don't know what the hell a Republican looked

37:44.705 --> 37:49.350
like, you see. I was very surprised that they were 
human and everything was fine.

37:57.498 --> 38:08.082
I continued to be a Democrat on up until 10 or 12 
years ago.

38:09.327 --> 38:10.949
And now you're a Republican? Yes. When they come 
out with the likes of McGovern as a candidate for

38:11.911 --> 38:20.322
president of the United States, I can't stomach 
that in any sense. And what did you think about

38:20.563 --> 38:25.910
Lyndon Johnson as far as his programs? Well, about 
his program,

38:26.271 --> 38:34.282
I don't, I didn't like it. I knew Lyndon Johnson 
pretty well. Had a good many occasions to do

38:41.805 --> 38:49.877
business with him, government business.

38:49.897 --> 38:52.501
And I have to admire a great many things about him. 
But there's some things that I don't admire about

38:54.344 --> 38:58.129
him, didn't admire about him.

39:03.597 --> 39:08.224
I think he understood an awful lot better what made 
Lyndon Johnson move than he did what made the

39:09.453 --> 39:15.619
United States move on a long-term basis. I think 
things that were important to Lyndon Johnson were

39:15.639 --> 39:31.674
a little more important to him sometimes than the 
good of his country, and I don't admire that on

39:15.639 --> 39:31.674
anybody, no matter how expedient it might be for 
the problem at hand. In other words, ever since

39:32.295 --> 39:37.059
McGovern in 1972, you voted, you've been a 
Republican. You betcha. And are you a member of the

39:39.237 --> 39:41.720
Republican Party? Did you ever get active in 
politics? Oh, yes. I'm a member of the Republican

39:44.243 --> 39:50.269
National Committee.

39:50.289 --> 40:05.987
I haven't been active in local politics,

39:50.289 --> 40:05.987
but reasonably active in national politics.

40:08.178 --> 40:26.258
that actually split ticket

40:08.178 --> 40:26.258
in a local sense,

40:08.178 --> 40:26.258
because the Republicans haven't put up the best 
candidates in some of these places. And when I can

40:26.278 --> 40:36.649
have a guy like Tiger Teague, who's a classmate of 
mine, and I suppose everybody knows what he did and

40:26.278 --> 40:36.649
what he stood for, Well, I'm going to arrange it so 
that I can vote for him. I guess never anybody. OK.

40:44.388 --> 40:45.910
Let's go back to A&M, then. Can you tell me, we 
talked about your employment there. Can you tell

40:49.335 --> 40:52.600
me about where you lived on campus for your four 
years? How were the accommodations?

40:59.350 --> 41:08.543
Well, I think in general, one would say that what we 
thought were very good accommodations then would

40:59.350 --> 41:08.543
be absolutely unacceptable. to the kids now, and I 
can't tell you whether this is good or bad, but I

41:09.299 --> 41:18.034
have my own notion about it.

41:19.557 --> 41:33.822
When I entered school and entered the Corps, I was 
assigned a D Battery or Field Artillery, which was

41:19.557 --> 41:33.822
the newest unit organized that year.

41:36.535 --> 41:46.770
And that battery was quartered in Foster Hall.

41:46.790 --> 41:56.844
So I spent that year, freshman year, and sophomore 
year in Foster Hall. And then the junior year, we

41:56.864 --> 42:06.137
moved over and were in Puryear Hall, which was 
brand new, just opened that year. and also a senior

42:08.075 --> 42:10.198
year. I was in first year hall. So the 
accommodations were pretty good for the time.

42:15.325 --> 42:18.770
They were wonderful as far as I'm concerned for the 
time. At that time there still were Hollywood, the

42:18.830 --> 42:34.572
huts and all of that, and I had a lot of friends that 
lived in them, spent a lot of time down there, and

42:18.830 --> 42:34.572
they weren't too bad either. didn't like very 
much, but they were all right. What was your

42:39.045 --> 42:40.267
opinion of hazing? Well, I thought it was 
wonderful actually. I realize

42:43.992 --> 42:58.332
how it sounds to say that,

42:43.992 --> 42:58.332
but I think it made people out of an awful lot of of 
individuals who might not otherwise have

42:59.628 --> 43:07.199
achieved that status. Well, what do you mean by 
that? Could you continue? I mean, I think it made

43:11.505 --> 43:23.762
for

43:11.505 --> 43:23.762
a deeper understanding of many kinds of values, 
including human values.

43:28.889 --> 43:52.924
And it created an understanding of discipline, 
not just discipline in a military sense, but

43:28.889 --> 43:52.924
discipline of thinking and discipline of conduct 
that

43:28.889 --> 43:52.924
kids growing up don't have automatically and now 
in most cases don't get. And I think it was good in

43:54.266 --> 43:58.592
that sense.

44:01.289 --> 44:04.413
It's true, I'm sure, that it can be abused. It was 
abused and has been since. But I'm also quite

44:09.799 --> 44:20.591
convinced that it isn't abused one-fifth as much 
as people would have you believe it was abused.

44:20.611 --> 44:29.001
Because the

44:20.611 --> 44:29.001
thing was handled in such way within the Corps when 
I was going up in it that if somebody, someone

44:31.411 --> 44:42.250
abused it very much, they were called on the carpet 
too, and they didn't get by with it. Little fringe

44:42.270 --> 44:47.239
areas, yeah, but I don't think they ever hurt 
anybody. How far could it go? Obviously it has to be

44:50.785 --> 44:52.949
some limits on it. Sure.

44:58.192 --> 45:03.941
Obviously also it had gone a little too far 
sometimes.

45:03.961 --> 45:08.367
I guess it was at about its height when I was here. I 
don't mean because I was here, but in looking at the

45:09.108 --> 45:18.502
situation it looked like it kind of peaked right 
along in those years and obviously it isn't

45:09.108 --> 45:18.502
anything like that now. No, not at all.

45:25.715 --> 45:48.162
So, while I can't deny that I was mighty, mighty 
happy when Fish Day came,

45:25.715 --> 45:48.162
I can also say that I enjoyed every weapon I ever 
got, except one or two, in which I thought things

45:25.715 --> 45:48.162
were abused, and I got lots of them. Well, were you 
sorry later on when they decreased the amount of

45:50.099 --> 45:54.525
hazing? I mean, there's almost no hazing at A&M in a 
physical sense, except for some push-ups, etc. In

45:58.469 --> 46:00.532
a physical sense, there's essentially none, 
that's right. Yes. Do you think that they should

46:01.133 --> 46:03.616
have continued the board? No. I was a member of the 
Century Council, and of course this question

46:03.716 --> 46:12.327
received quite a lot of consideration.

46:15.731 --> 46:19.836
And I had to vote for it going like it is going. In 
other words, decreasing hands. Decreasing,

46:21.725 --> 46:23.647
physically. Not because it was bad, but because 
you can't get something as big as the school was

46:24.448 --> 46:33.921
visualized to be on the course as it is. And have 
these kind of things

46:35.683 --> 46:48.861
going on in a routine way, because it's very 
bigness kills its effectiveness and breeds

46:50.360 --> 46:56.117
abuse.

